Super indulgent and packed full of flavour, The Big Pig is your favourite burger brought to the next level.

== Cheesy Bacon Chips ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%g}.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

== Burgers and Bacon ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @Breadcrumbs{10%g}, @Salt{¼%tsp} and @Water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs (see pantry for both amounts), then add the @British Pork Mince{240%g}. Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto one side of a lightly oiled baking tray. Lay the @British Streaky Bacon{6%rasher(s)} on the other side.

Bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

When the chips have 10 mins left, sprinkle the cheese over them, toss together and pop back into the oven for the remaining time.

== Slaw and Buns ==

When the burgers and bacon have 5 mins remaining, toss the @Coleslaw Mix{120%g} and @Burger Sauce{45%g} together in a medium bowl.

Halve the @Burger Buns{2}. Pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once the bacon is cooked, transfer half the rashers to a #chopping board{} and roughly chop.

Pour the @Maple Syrup{1%sachet} over the remaining rashers and turn to coat.

When everything's ready, spread the @Mayonnaise{64%g} over the bun bases. Top with the burgers, maple bacon rashers and the @Wild Rocket{20%g}. Sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve your craft burgers with the cheesy chips and slaw on the side.

Scatter the chopped crispy bacon over the chips to finish. Enjoy!